CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F431A1774530670
OL,3,CResearch finds 'Man's Best Friend'
OL,4,Cexisted more than 14,000 years ago
OL,6,FThe findings, published in Nature
OL,7,Fmagazine, focus on DNA analysis of the
OL,8,F14,300-year-old remains discovered in
OL,9,FGough's Cave and given to the Natural
OL,10,FHistory Museum by the 5th Marquess of
OL,11,FBath, the owner of Cheddar.
OL,13,FThe cave was also home to Cheddar Man,
OL,14,Fthe oldest near-complete modern human
OL,15,Fskeleton found in Britain. It was
OL,16,Fdiscovered there in 1903 and dates
OL,17,Fback to the Mesolithic era, about
OL,18,F10,000 years ago.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/7
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,432,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43103
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F431A1774530670
OL,3,CResearch finds 'Man's Best Friend'
OL,4,Cexisted more than 14,000 years ago
OL,6,FDr William Marsh from the Natural
OL,7,FHistory Museum, who was lead author of
OL,8,Fthe study, said: "We ran DNA analysis
OL,9,Fon several specimens from the museum's
OL,10,Ffossil mammal collection that had been
OL,11,Fexcavated from Gough's Cave.
OL,13,F"We found that one of them was
OL,14,Fgenetically closer to a dog than a
OL,15,Fwolf. This was a fantastic finding
OL,16,Fthat, at the time, represented the
OL,17,Foldest empirical evidence of dogs."
OL,26,@pD@ROUuD@AOUyD@cO]
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/7
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,432,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43104
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F431A1774530670
OL,3,CResearch finds 'Man's Best Friend'
OL,4,Cexisted more than 14,000 years ago
OL,6,FFurther research then discovered even
OL,7,Folder dog remains at another cave site
OL,8,Fin Turkey as well as at three other
OL,9,Fsites in Central Europe. The Cheddar
OL,10,Fdiscovery remains the oldest in the UK.
OL,12,FFenia Vitali, General Manager at
OL,13,FCheddar Gorge and Caves, said: "To
OL,14,Fhave both the oldest nearly complete
OL,15,Fhuman skeleton and the earliest
OL,16,Fexample of a domesticated dog in
OL,17,FEurope, indeed one of two in the
OL,18,Fworld, found at Cheddar is quite
OL,19,Fincredible and we look forward to
OL,20,Fsharing more information with our
OL,21,Fvisitors in the coming months.
OL,26,@uD@`OU
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/7
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,432,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43105
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F431A1774530670
OL,3,CResearch finds 'Man's Best Friend'
OL,4,Cexisted more than 14,000 years ago
OL,6,F"We're delighted to have been working
OL,7,Fwith the with Natural History Museum
OL,8,Fover many decades and are excited to
OL,9,Fsee what discoveries are made in the
OL,10,Ffuture."
OL,12,FCeawlin Thynn, the 8th Marquess of
OL,13,FBath, said: "Ongoing research on
OL,14,FCheddar finds continues to inform and
OL,15,Fexpand our knowledge of the lives of
OL,16,Four ancient ancestors.
OL,26,@nD@AOUrD@HO]uD@MOU
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/7
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
